<!-- ── PMO Loop ────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section pmo-loop" aria-label="The PMO cycle">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-center fade-in">
      <div class="section-label">The Loop</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Five steps. Infinite scale.</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading">The PMO cycle runs continuously across every project simultaneously.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps fade-in delay-1" role="list">
      <div class="step" role="listitem">
        <div class="step-number">01</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <span class="step-icon">📡</span>
          <h3>Scan</h3>
          <p>Dashboard scans all repos every 3 minutes. CI status, open PRs, uncommitted changes — everything at a glance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step" role="listitem">
        <div class="step-number">02</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <span class="step-icon">🎯</span>
          <h3>Prioritize</h3>
          <p>You decide where to direct attention. Dashboard tells you — you choose. Minimal cognitive load, maximum leverage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step" role="listitem">
        <div class="step-number">03</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <span class="step-icon">🚀</span>
          <h3>Dispatch</h3>
          <p>Drop agents into standardized repos. Same build targets, same CI, same lint commands. No setup. No babysitting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step" role="listitem">
        <div class="step-number">04</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <span class="step-icon">📊</span>
          <h3>Monitor</h3>
          <p>TMC orchestrates agent coordination. Agents lock files, register intent, avoid conflicts. You watch the dashboard.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step" role="listitem">
        <div class="step-number">05</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <span class="step-icon">✅</span>
          <h3>Review &amp; Ship</h3>
          <p>Code arrives production-ready. Lint, tests, coverage — all passed. You review intent, not whether it works.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

